Q1) Write a Java program that reads a sentence from the user, splits it into words, and then counts the frequency 
of each word using a HashMap. Display the word frequency.

Q2) Write a Java program that removes all duplicate characters from a string, retaining the order of 
the first occurrence of each character.
Use a HashMap for this task.

Q3) Write a Java program that merges two HashMaps. If a key exists in both maps, 
sum the values from both maps.

Q4) Write a Java program that uses a HashMap to find the length of 
the longest substring without repeating characters 
in a given string.

Q5) Write a Java program that groups characters in a string by their frequency (characters with the same 
frequency should be grouped together).